      %h2 Welcome to the BBC Capstone Project Homepage!
      %h5 Project Description:
      %p
        The Automatic Generator Battery Backup Charger (or simply
        =succeed "," do
          %b BBC
        as we call it) is a hardware system regulated by an
        =link_to "Adruino Uno", "https://store.arduino.cc/usa/arduino-uno-rev3"
        microcontroller.
        %br
        %br
        The
        %b BBC
        connects to general purpose generators and monitors the charge of the internal battery. When the charge of the battery drops below a threshold of
        =succeed "," do
          %i 11.5V
        the
        %b BBC
        attempts to automatically fire-up the generator for a user specified amount of time. Once the charge on the internal battery reaches a separate threshold of
        =succeed "," do
          %i 14.0V
        the
        %b BBC
        turns off the generator and waits for the voltage to deplete again, and repeats.
        %br
        %br
        An
        =link_to "Arduino LCD Keypad Shield", "https://www.dfrobot.com/wiki/index.php/Arduino_LCD_KeyPad_Shield_(SKU:_DFR0009)"
        shows live information about the charge of the generator's internal battery and allows the user to control the starter time. If the attached generator does not start within the alotted amount of time and iterations, the
        %b BBC
        system displays an error message (
        %i Starter Failure!
        ) and the system must be reset. This is to reduce the likelyhood of the starter and generator from burning out.

